{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-81e347f47d2f3452", "type": "tool_result", "content": "{\n    \"query\": \"Perch 2.0 bioacoustics foundation model van Merrienboer 2025 SOTA species detection\",\n    \"follow_up_questions\": null,\n    \"answer\": \"Perch 2.0 is a state-of-the-art bioacoustics foundation model for species detection, trained on over 14,000 species, and capable of transfer learning for new species classification tasks. It was released in 2025 and has shown strong performance in both terrestrial and underwater acoustics.\",\n    \"images\": [],\n    \"results\": [\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/394362751_Perch_20_The_Bittern_Lesson_for_Bioacoustics\",\n            \"title\": \"(PDF) Perch 2.0: The Bittern Lesson for Bioacoustics\",\n            \"content\": \"Perch 2.0 is a supervised bioacoustics foundation model pretrained on 14,597 species, including birds, mammals, amphibians, and insects, and\",\n            \"score\": 0.6493346,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mgfNowaxYu\",\n            \"title\": \"Perch 2.0: The Bittern Lesson for Bioacoustics\",\n            \"content\": \"by B van Merri\\u00ebnboer \\u00b7 Cited by 36 \\u2014 Perch 2.0 is a compact bioacoustic model trained on ~14 000 species and event classes to produce general-purpose audio embeddings.\",\n            \"score\": 0.6479992,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.reddit.com/r/mlscaling/comments/1sxno0o/perch_20_the_bittern_lesson_for_bioacoustics_van\",\n            \"title\": \"\\\"Perch 2.0: The Bittern Lesson for Bioacoustics\\\", van ...\",\n            \"content\": \"\\\"Perch 2.0: The Bittern Lesson for Bioacoustics\\\", van Merri\\u00ebnboer et al 2025 (12m-parameter animal sound CNN classifier: 14k species, 1.5m\",\n            \"score\": 0.6356076,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/perch-2-0\",\n            \"title\": \"Perch 2.0: Advanced Multi-taxa Bioacoustics\",\n            \"content\": \"Perch 2.0 is a state-of-the-art bioacoustic model engineered for large-scale, fine-grained species classification and robust transfer learning\",\n            \"score\": 0.6097339,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://research.google/blog/how-ai-trained-on-birds-is-surfacing-underwater-mysteries\",\n            \"title\": \"How AI trained on birds is surfacing underwater mysteries\",\n            \"content\": \"We describe how Perch 2.0, Google DeepMind's bioacoustics foundation model, trained on birds and other terrestrial animal vocalizations, transfers \\u2018whale\\u2019 to underwater acoustics challenges with \\u2018killer\\u2019 performance. In August 2025, Google DeepMind released the latest Perch foundational bioacoustics model, Perch 2.0, a bioacoustics foundation model trained primarily on birds and other terrestrial vocalizing animals. We are also sharing an end-to-end tutorial in Google Colab for our agile modeling workflow, demonstrating how to use Perch 2.0 to create a custom classifier for whale vocalizations using the NOAA NCEI Passive Acoustic Data Archive through Google Cloud. In bioacoustics transfer learning, the pre-trained model (such as Perch 2.0) is used to produce embeddings for each window of audio. To create a new custom model for any set of labeled audio data, we apply the pre-trained model to the audio data to get the embeddings, which are used as the input features for a logistic regression classifier.\",\n            \"score\": 0.5769478,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        }\n    ],\n    \"response_time\": 2.37,\n    \"request_id\": \"9cf2730a-37c5-4402-87d7-601d5ce85c4a\"\n}", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "17655fbc-45e8-4593-9dec-7803abc06d07", "uuid": "28ce3f1e-406d-4d30-93fc-890b01830f78", "timestamp": "2026-07-16T06:14:49.475Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "{\n    \"query\": \"Perch 2.0 bioacoustics foundation model van Merrienboer 2025 SOTA species detection\",\n    \"follow_up_questions\": null,\n    \"answer\": \"Perch 2.0 is a state-of-the-art bioacoustics foundation model for species detection, trained on over 14,000 species, and capable of transfer learning for new species classification tasks. It was released in 2025 and has shown strong performance in both terrestrial and underwater acoustics.\",\n    \"images\": [],\n    \"results\": [\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/394362751_Perch_20_The_Bittern_Lesson_for_Bioacoustics\",\n            \"title\": \"(PDF) Perch 2.0: The Bittern Lesson for Bioacoustics\",\n            \"content\": \"Perch 2.0 is a supervised bioacoustics foundation model pretrained on 14,597 species, including birds, mammals, amphibians, and insects, and\",\n            \"score\": 0.6493346,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mgfNowaxYu\",\n            \"title\": \"Perch 2.0: The Bittern Lesson for Bioacoustics\",\n            \"content\": \"by B van Merri\\u00ebnboer \\u00b7 Cited by 36 \\u2014 Perch 2.0 is a compact bioacoustic model trained on ~14 000 species and event classes to produce general-purpose audio embeddings.\",\n            \"score\": 0.6479992,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.reddit.com/r/mlscaling/comments/1sxno0o/perch_20_the_bittern_lesson_for_bioacoustics_van\",\n            \"title\": \"\\\"Perch 2.0: The Bittern Lesson for Bioacoustics\\\", van ...\",\n            \"content\": \"\\\"Perch 2.0: The Bittern Lesson for Bioacoustics\\\", van Merri\\u00ebnboer et al 2025 (12m-parameter animal sound CNN classifier: 14k species, 1.5m\",\n            \"score\": 0.6356076,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/perch-2-0\",\n            \"title\": \"Perch 2.0: Advanced Multi-taxa Bioacoustics\",\n            \"content\": \"Perch 2.0 is a state-of-the-art bioacoustic model engineered for large-scale, fine-grained species classification and robust transfer learning\",\n            \"score\": 0.6097339,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://research.google/blog/how-ai-trained-on-birds-is-surfacing-underwater-mysteries\",\n            \"title\": \"How AI trained on birds is surfacing underwater mysteries\",\n            \"content\": \"We describe how Perch 2.0, Google DeepMind's bioacoustics foundation model, trained on birds and other terrestrial animal vocalizations, transfers \\u2018whale\\u2019 to underwater acoustics challenges with \\u2018killer\\u2019 performance. In August 2025, Google DeepMind released the latest Perch foundational bioacoustics model, Perch 2.0, a bioacoustics foundation model trained primarily on birds and other terrestrial vocalizing animals. We are also sharing an end-to-end tutorial in Google Colab for our agile modeling workflow, demonstrating how to use Perch 2.0 to create a custom classifier for whale vocalizations using the NOAA NCEI Passive Acoustic Data Archive through Google Cloud. In bioacoustics transfer learning, the pre-trained model (such as Perch 2.0) is used to produce embeddings for each window of audio. To create a new custom model for any set of labeled audio data, we apply the pre-trained model to the audio data to get the embeddings, which are used as the input features for a logistic regression classifier.\",\n            \"score\": 0.5769478,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        }\n    ],\n    \"response_time\": 2.37,\n    \"request_id\": \"9cf2730a-37c5-4402-87d7-601d5ce85c4a\"\n}", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-a785ead41e3cedb7", "type": "tool_result", "content": "{\n    \"query\": \"metadata auxiliary supervision multi-task learning audio bioacoustics prior work\",\n    \"follow_up_questions\": null,\n    \"answer\": \"Multi-task learning in audio bioacoustics uses auxiliary supervision to improve classification of whale calls. Recent advances focus on self-supervised pre-training and feature-informed captioning. Computational bioacoustics leverages deep learning for species identification.\",\n    \"images\": [],\n    \"results\": [\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.amazon.science/publications/multi-task-self-supervised-pre-training-for-music-classification\",\n            \"title\": \"Multi-task self-supervised pre-training for music classification\",\n            \"content\": \"by HH Wu \\u00b7 2021 \\u00b7 Cited by 54 \\u2014 In this paper, we apply self-supervised and multi-task learning methods for pre-training music encoders, and explore various design choices including encoder\",\n            \"score\": 0.14512776,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://arxiv.org/html/2506.15154v1\",\n            \"title\": \"Multi-Task Learning for Music Feature-Informed Captioning\",\n            \"content\": \"# SonicVerse: Multi-Task Learning for Music Feature-Informed Captioning. This paper introduces a multi-task music captioning model, SonicVerse , that integrates caption generation with auxiliary music feature detection tasks such as key detection, vocals detection, and more, so as to directly capture both low-level acoustic details as well as high-level musical attributes. This framework not only produces rich, descriptive captions for short music fragments but also directly enables the generation of detailed time-informed descriptions for longer music pieces, by chaining the outputs using a large-language model. To train the model, we extended the MusicBench dataset by annotating it with music features using MIRFLEX, a modular music feature extractor, resulting in paired audio, captions and music feature data. We propose that by training a model to generate detailed captions on short segments, these can then be chained using a Large Language Model to produce comprehensive captions that encompass the musical features as well as the temporal evolution of the piece.\",\n            \"score\": 0.13178682,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3417/13/9/5239\",\n            \"title\": \"JSUM: A Multitask Learning Speech Recognition Model for Jointly Supervised and Unsupervised Learning\",\n            \"content\": \"permission is required to reuse all or part of the article published by MDPI, including figures and tables. However, the training of end-to-end speech recognition models typically necessitates a significant quantity of supervised data to achieve good performance, which poses a challenge in low-resource conditions. This paper proposes a joint supervised and unsupervised multi-task learning model (JSUM). Our approach leverages the unsupervised pre-trained wav2vec 2.0 model as a shared encoder that integrates the joint CTC-Attention network and the generative adversarial network into a unified end-to-end architecture. end-to-end speech recognition; multitasking learning; supervised learning; unsupervised learning. Recent advances in deep learning architectures with a high degree of parameterization have led to the development of end-to-end approaches, which have demonstrated their effectiveness in achieving state-of-the-art performance in automatic speech recognition (ASR) tasks, as shown in several studies [1,2,3]. Current work on end-to-end speech recognition focuses on two approaches: CTC [4,5,6] and attention-mechanism-based encoder\\u2013decoder [7,8,9]. used multi-language datasets based on the joint CTC-Attention architecture for end-to-end speech recognition.\",\n            \"score\": 0.13118461,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8944344\",\n            \"title\": \"Computational bioacoustics with deep learning: a review and roadmap\",\n            \"content\": \"# Computational bioacoustics with deep learning: a review and roadmap. Methods are inherited from the wider field of deep learning, including speech and image processing. In this paper I perform a review of the state of the art in deep learning for computational bioacoustics, aiming to clarify key concepts and identify and analyse knowledge gaps. Based on this, I offer a subjective but principled roadmap for computational bioacoustics with deep learning: topics that the community should aim to address, in order to make the most of future developments in AI and informatics, and to use audio data in answering zoological and ecological questions. I then offer a \\u2018roadmap\\u2019 of work in deep learning for computational bioacoustics, based on the survey and thematic analysis, and drawing in topics from the wider field of deep learning as well as broad topics in bioacoustics.\",\n            \"score\": 0.11400327,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://dl.acm.org/doi/full/10.1145/3784941.3785440\",\n            \"title\": \"Improving the Classification of Humpback Whale Calls ...\",\n            \"content\": \"This section reviews prior research in four major areas: (i) deep learning for whale vocalizations, (ii) metadata and contextual information,\",\n            \"score\": 0.08981337,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        }\n    ],\n    \"response_time\": 1.3,\n    \"request_id\": \"81e37ad5-14fa-4fb1-a003-b1eadd331c36\"\n}", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "17655fbc-45e8-4593-9dec-7803abc06d07", "uuid": "19fe30cb-a6bd-4119-