nnotating it with music features using MIRFLEX, a modular music feature extractor, resulting in paired audio, captions and music feature data. We propose that by training a model to generate detailed captions on short segments, these can then be chained using a Large Language Model to produce comprehensive captions that encompass the musical features as well as the temporal evolution of the piece.\",\n            \"score\": 0.13178682,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3417/13/9/5239\",\n            \"title\": \"JSUM: A Multitask Learning Speech Recognition Model for Jointly Supervised and Unsupervised Learning\",\n            \"content\": \"permission is required to reuse all or part of the article published by MDPI, including figures and tables. However, the training of end-to-end speech recognition models typically necessitates a significant quantity of supervised data to achieve good performance, which poses a challenge in low-resource conditions. This paper proposes a joint supervised and unsupervised multi-task learning model (JSUM). Our approach leverages the unsupervised pre-trained wav2vec 2.0 model as a shared encoder that integrates the joint CTC-Attention network and the generative adversarial network into a unified end-to-end architecture. end-to-end speech recognition; multitasking learning; supervised learning; unsupervised learning. Recent advances in deep learning architectures with a high degree of parameterization have led to the development of end-to-end approaches, which have demonstrated their effectiveness in achieving state-of-the-art performance in automatic speech recognition (ASR) tasks, as shown in several studies [1,2,3]. Current work on end-to-end speech recognition focuses on two approaches: CTC [4,5,6] and attention-mechanism-based encoder\\u2013decoder [7,8,9]. used multi-language datasets based on the joint CTC-Attention architecture for end-to-end speech recognition.\",\n            \"score\": 0.13118461,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8944344\",\n            \"title\": \"Computational bioacoustics with deep learning: a review and roadmap\",\n            \"content\": \"# Computational bioacoustics with deep learning: a review and roadmap. Methods are inherited from the wider field of deep learning, including speech and image processing. In this paper I perform a review of the state of the art in deep learning for computational bioacoustics, aiming to clarify key concepts and identify and analyse knowledge gaps. Based on this, I offer a subjective but principled roadmap for computational bioacoustics with deep learning: topics that the community should aim to address, in order to make the most of future developments in AI and informatics, and to use audio data in answering zoological and ecological questions. I then offer a \\u2018roadmap\\u2019 of work in deep learning for computational bioacoustics, based on the survey and thematic analysis, and drawing in topics from the wider field of deep learning as well as broad topics in bioacoustics.\",\n            \"score\": 0.11400327,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://dl.acm.org/doi/full/10.1145/3784941.3785440\",\n            \"title\": \"Improving the Classification of Humpback Whale Calls ...\",\n            \"content\": \"This section reviews prior research in four major areas: (i) deep learning for whale vocalizations, (ii) metadata and contextual information,\",\n            \"score\": 0.08981337,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        }\n    ],\n    \"response_time\": 1.3,\n    \"request_id\": \"81e37ad5-14fa-4fb1-a003-b1eadd331c36\"\n}", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-9b0c0dc6e479fe00", "type": "tool_result", "content": "{\n    \"query\": \"BirdSet BEANS WABAD bioacoustics benchmark SOTA 2025\",\n    \"follow_up_questions\": null,\n    \"answer\": \"BirdSet is a large-scale dataset for avian bioacoustics, featuring over 520,000 recordings for training and diverse testing protocols. It aims to improve deep learning model evaluation in passive acoustic monitoring. The dataset is used for benchmarking and includes comprehensive training and evaluation protocols.\",\n    \"images\": [],\n    \"results\": [\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://arxiv.org/html/2403.10380v3\",\n            \"title\": \"BirdSet: A Dataset and Benchmark for Classification in Avian Bioacoustics\",\n            \"content\": \"# BirdSet: A Dataset and Benchmark for Classification in Avian Bioacoustics. To maximize the potential of cost-effective and minimal-invasive passive acoustic monitoring (PAM), DL models must analyze bird vocalizations across a wide range of species and environmental conditions. However, data fragmentation challenges a comprehensive evaluation of generalization performance. Therefore, we introduce the BirdSet dataset, comprising approximately 520,000 global bird recordings for training and over 400 hours of PAM recordings for testing. Our benchmark offers baselines for several DL models to enhance comparability and consolidate research across studies, along with code implementations that include comprehensive training and evaluation protocols. The most prominent task in PAM is the detection and classification of bird vocalizations in long-duration soundscape recordings. *Reproducibility* is challenged by the absence of unified training protocols and the employment of custom datasets from XC, leading to a lack of a common dataset and diverse pre-processing (e.g., event detection).\",\n            \"score\": 0.46920466,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dRXxFEY8ZE\",\n            \"title\": \"BirdSet: A Large-Scale Dataset for Audio Classification in ...\",\n            \"content\": \"by L Rauch \\u00b7 Cited by 51 \\u2014 We introduce BirdSet, a large-scale benchmark data set for audio classification focusing on avian bioacoustics.Read more\",\n            \"score\": 0.42821008,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://huggingface.co/datasets/DBD-research-group/BirdSet\",\n            \"title\": \"DBD-research-group/BirdSet \\u00b7 Datasets at Hugging Face\",\n            \"content\": \"# Datasets: --- DBD-research-group / BirdSet like 28 Follow DBD-research-group 35. Make sure to review how to configure the dataset viewer, and open a discussion for direct support. ## BirdSet. Deep learning (DL) has greatly advanced audio classification, yet the field is limited by the scarcity of large-scale benchmark datasets that have propelled. While AudioSet aims to bridge this gap as a universal-domain dataset, its restricted accessibility and lack of diverse real-world. benchmark dataset for audio classification focusing on avian bioacoustics. ## Note that Birdset supports datasets<=3.6.0 version, we are looking into updates to support the newest version. Each dataset (except for XCM and XCL that only feature Train) comes with a dataset dictionary that features **Train**, **Test\\\\_5s**, and **Test**:. dataset = load_dataset(\\\"DBD-research-group/BirdSet\\\", \\\"HSN\\\"). | ebird\\\\_code\\\\_multilabel | Sequence(datasets.ClassLabel(names=class\\\\_list)) | assigned species label in a multilabel format |. | detected\\\\_events | Sequence(datasets.Sequence(datasets.Value(\\\"float64\\\"))) | only traindata: detected audio events in a recording with bambird, tuples of start/end time |.\",\n            \"score\": 0.40938663,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://github.com/DBD-research-group/BirdSet\",\n            \"title\": \"GitHub - DBD-research-group/BirdSet: A benchmark dataset collection for bird sound classification \\u00b7 GitHub\",\n            \"content\": \"## Use saved searches to filter your results more quickly. # $\\\\texttt{BirdSet}$ - A Large-Scale Dataset for Audio Classification in Avian Bioacoustics \\ud83e\\udd17. Therefore, we introduce $\\\\texttt{BirdSet}$, a large-scale benchmark dataset for audio classification focusing on avian bioacoustics. | **Auxiliary** | POW | Powdermill Nature soundscape validation dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset of XCL. | **Test & Dedicated Train** | PER | Amazon Basin soundscape test dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset. | NES | Columbia Costa Rica soundscape test dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset. |  | UHH | Hawaiian Islands soundscape test dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset. |  | HSN | High Sierras Nevada soundscape test dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset. |  | NBP | NIPS4BPlus test dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset. |  | SNE | Sierre Nevada soundscape test dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset. To run an experiment, use the following command in the directory of the repository:.\",\n            \"score\": 0.4013364,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/BirdSet%3A-A-Large-Scale-Dataset-for-Audio-in-Avian-Rauch-Schwinger/716fd0d35a09f6363b7b522b7979ae7ace6d6ccf\",\n            \"title\": \"BirdSet: A Large-Scale Dataset for Audio Classification in ...\",\n            \"content\": \"Bird set is introduced, a large-scale benchmark dataset for audio classification focusing on avian bioacoustics and six well-known DL models in multi-label ...Read more\",\n            \"score\": 0.3967697,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        }\n    ],\n    \"response_time\": 1.9,\n    \"request_id\": \"28749681-7a35-44f3-974f-6af762d32281\"\n}", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "17655fbc-45e8-4593-9dec-7803abc06d07", "uuid": "4fdbc135-c58c-4338-bd42-66cc8c1c8635", "timestamp": "2026-07-16T06:14:54.145Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "{\n    \"query\": \"BirdSet BEANS WABAD bioacoustics benchmark SOTA 2025\",\n    \"follow_up_questions\": null,\n    \"answer\": \"BirdSet is a large-scale dataset for avian bioacoustics, featuring over 520,000 recordings for training and diverse testing protocols. It aims to improve deep learning model evaluation in passive acoustic monitoring. The dataset is used for benchmarking and includes comprehensive training and evaluation protocols.\",\n    \"images\": [],\n    \"results\": [\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://arxiv.org/html/2403.10380v3\",\n            \"title\": \"BirdSet: A Dataset and Benchmark for Classification in Avian Bioacoustics\",\n            \"content\": \"# BirdSet: A Dataset and Benchmark for Classification in Avian Bioacoustics. To maximize the potential of cost-effective and minimal-invasive passive acoustic monitoring (PAM), DL models must analyze bird vocalizations across a wide range of species and environmental conditions. However, data fragmentation challenges a comprehensive evaluation of generalization performance. Therefore, we introduce the BirdSet dataset, comprising approximately 520,000 global bird recordings for training and over 400 hours of PAM recordings for testing. Our benchmark offers baselines for several DL models to enhance comparability and consolidate research across studies, along with code implementations that include comprehensive training and evaluation protocols. The most prominent task in PAM is the detection and classification of bird vocalizations in long-duration soundscape recordings. *Reproducibility* is challenged by the absence of unified training protocols and the employment of custom datasets from XC, leading to a lack of a common dataset and diverse pre-processing (e.g., event detection).\",\n            \"score\": 0.46920466,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dRXxFEY8ZE\",\n            \"title\": \"BirdSet: A Large-Scale Dataset for Audio Classification in ...\",\n            \"content\": \"by L Rauch \\u00b7 Cited by 51 \\u2014 We introduce BirdSet, a large-scale benchmark data set for audio classification focusing on avian bioacoustics.Read more\",\n            \"score\": 0.42821008,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://huggingface.co/datasets/DBD-research-group/BirdSet\",\n            \"title\": \"DBD-research-group/BirdSet \\u00b7 Datasets at Hugging Face\",\n            \"content\": \"# Datasets: --- DBD-research-group / BirdSet like 28 Follow DBD-research-group 35. Make sure to review how to configure the dataset viewer, and open a discussion for direct support. ## BirdSet. Deep learning (DL) has greatly advanced audio classification, yet the field is limited by the scarcity of large-scale benchmark datasets that have propelled. While AudioSet aims to bridge this gap as a universal-domain dataset, its restricted accessibility and lack of diverse real-world. benchmark dataset for audio classification focusing on avian bioacoustics. ## Note that Birdset supports datasets<=3.6.0 version, we are looking into updates to support the newest version. Each dataset (except for XCM and XCL that only feature Train) comes with a dataset dictionary that features **Train**, **Test\\\\_5s**, and **Test**:. dataset = load_dataset(\\\"DBD-research-group/BirdSet\\\", \\\"HSN\\\"). | ebird\\\\_code\\\\_multilabel | Sequence(datasets.ClassLabel(names=class\\\\_list)) | assigned species label in a multilabel format |. | detected\\\\_events | Sequence(datasets.Sequence(datasets.Value(\\\"float64\\\"))) | only traindata: detected audio events in a recording with bambird, tuples of start/end time |.\",\n            \"score\": 0.40938663,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://github.com/DBD-research-group/BirdSet\",\n            \"title\": \"GitHub - DBD-research-group/BirdSet: A benchmark dataset collection for bird sound classification \\u00b7 GitHub\",\n            \"content\": \"## Use saved searches to filter your results more quickly. # $\\\\texttt{BirdSet}$ - A Large-Scale Dataset for Audio Classification in Avian Bioacoustics \\ud83e\\udd17. Therefore, we introduce $\\\\texttt{BirdSet}$, a large-scale benchmark dataset for audio classification focusing on avian bioacoustics. | **Auxiliary** | POW | Powdermill Nature soundscape validation dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset of XCL. | **Test & Dedicated Train** | PER | Amazon Basin soundscape test dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset. | NES | Columbia Costa Rica soundscape test dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset. |  | UHH | Hawaiian Islands soundscape test dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset. |  | HSN | High Sierras Nevada soundscape test dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset. |  | NBP | NIPS4BPlus test dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset. |  | SNE | Sierre Nevada soundscape test dataset and class-dedicated focal training subset. To run an experiment, use the following command in the directory of the repository:.\",\n            \"score\": 0.4013364,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/BirdSet%3A-A-Large-Scale-Dataset-for-Audio-in-Avian-Rauch-Schwinger/716fd0d35a09f6363b7b522b7979ae7ace6d6ccf\",\n            \"title\": \"BirdSet: A Large-Scale Dataset for Audio Classification in ...\",\n            \"content\": \"Bird set is introduced, a large-scale benchmark dataset for audio classification focusing on avian bioacoustics and six well-known 